# NodeJS Build
## ðŸ”¹ Jenkins Pipeline â€” NodeJS Build
we will learn how to **install dependencies, run tests, and build a NodeJS project**.

pipeline {
    agent any
    tools {
        nodejs 'NodeJS-16'
    }
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git url: 'git@github.com:sumit-pathnex/jan2026_pathnex_sumit.git'
            }
        }
        stage('Install Dependencies') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm install'
            }
        }
        stage('Run Tests') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm test'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm run build'
            }
        }
    }
}

## ðŸ”¹ GitLab CI â€” NodeJS Build

stages:
  - install
  - test
  - build

node-install:
  stage: install
  image: node:16
  script:
    - git clone  'git@github.com:sumit-pathnex/jan2026_pathnexa-sumit.git'

    - cd sumit-pathnex-app
    - npm install

node-test:
  stage: test
  image: node:16
  script:
    - cd sumit-pathnex-app
    - npm test

node-build:
  stage: build
  image: node:16
  script:
    - cd lucky_pathnex-app
    - npm run build
